heading: Is a better level of education a job guarantee?
subheading: In 2023, the employment rate of the population with a higher education qualification reached 86.3%.
textNote: The employment rate is calculated for people aged between 20 and 64 with a high level of education. Tertiary education corresponds to ISCED levels 5-8. For a low level of education (ISCED levels 0-2), the rate is 58.3%.; for a medium level (ISCED levels 3-4) it is 74.6%.
